               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18390408-1395-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1395-18390408 t18390408-1395-offence-1 t18390408-1395-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1395. <persName id="def1-1395-18390408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1395-18390408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1395-18390408" type="age" value="30"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1395-18390408" type="surname" value="HOLSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1395-18390408" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES HOLSTON</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390408-1395-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1395-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1395-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390408-cd-230" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390408-1395-offence-1 t18390408-cd-230"></join>9th of April</rs>, 2 yards of woollen cloth, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390408-name-1363" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1363" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1363" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1363" type="given" value="VINCENT"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390408-1395-offence-1 t18390408-name-1363"></join>Vincent Daniels</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1364" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1364" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1364" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1364" type="given" value="VINCENT"></interp>VINCENT DANIELS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Brewer-street, and am a woollen draper. On the 9th of April, the prisoner came in with two patterns of silk, and asked if I could match them—I said I could not—he then untied a piece of, cloth, and asked if I could match that—I said I could not—he asked me to show him the nearest I had, and while I was getting that, there was a remnant of cloth on the counter, which he tied up—he said the cloth I showed him was not near enough, and was going out—when he got to the door, I asked him to walk in again—he came in and said, "For God's sake Mr. Daniels don't do it, I will give you it back."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Do you state that I took the cloth, tied it in my hand-kerchief, and went to the door? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I collared you at the door—a young man came to the door, and I sent him for the policeman—the pri<lb></lb>soner said, "No, I will pay Mr. Daniels for it"—he ran behind the counter, untied the cloth and his own garment, threw it under the counter, and said, "What have I got of yours?"—he had no money about him, only a flash note—when the policeman came, he was in the middle of the shop—I had hold of his arm—he had got out of the house when I took him back—when the policeman came I fetched this piece of, cloth from</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183904080191"></xptr>
               <p>under the counter—I did not select it from a number of pieces on the counter.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Do you swear that he tied it up in his handkerchief, and took it out of the door? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, he got down three steps—he tied up his little coat first, then opened one corner, and tied up this cloth.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1365" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1365" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1365" type="surname" value="MURCH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1365" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MURCH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi> 106.) I was sent for—when I got to the shop, the prosecutor was holding the prisoner by the arm—he said he had taken a piece of cloth—Mr. Daniels went behind the counter and picked up the cloth—I searched the prisoner at the station-house, and found no money on him, but a pocket-book, and a flash note.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I said I had a half-sovereign and a half-crown. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, you did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I had a little portion of a tunic coat in the bundle, and I wanted to make a pair of towsers to match it for my own child, and to match some waistcoats—he said he had not got it—my little coat was then lying on the pieces of cloth. I took the coat and tied it up in my bundle—he was looking at me all the time—it is not likely I should take any thing else—I had not stepped beyond the threshold of the door—he took me and told a young man to fetch a policeman—I said, "For what?"—he said. "If you don't know what is your own, I will tell you"—I said, "I have nothing but what I paid for"—I did not say, "I will pay you"—he se<lb></lb>lected this from a quantity of pieces, and I said, "If you are so inclined, why not take the first piece that comes to hand?"—that note was put into my hand one day in the street.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18390408-1395-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-1395-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-1395-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 30.—
<rs id="t18390408-1395-punishment-228" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1395-punishment-228" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
